gabe, die damit weitere Auseinandersetzung mit Gestalt und Wirkung des Genre der Marienklagen ermöglicht.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aChristian drama, GermanxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman dramayTo 1500xHistory and criticism. 4aBernhardstraktat. 4aMarienklage. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Medieval.2bisacsh  aPieta.  atreatise of Bernhard.1 aBüttner, Edgar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüttner, Edgar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cprintz978311048656840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311053186240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110531862423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110531862/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017